@Nik  Actually, it's just long enough if you use it correctly.  Place the lock  your rear tire/rim, there should be enough distance to now place it around a bike rack, or any reasonable sized post. There is no need to loop it around any part of the frame because the wheel cannot be pulled through the rear triangle.  Presto! your bike is locked securely, and the lock is small enough that they cannot open it with a hydraulic jack like they can larger locks.

Cheers,
Mike

